@page "/markdown-view"
<h3>MarkdownView Component</h3>
<p>The MarkdownView component renders a Markdown string as HTML, using the Markdig library with advanced extensions enabled.
   It integrates via an injected <code>IMarkdownRenderer</code> service and supports all standard Markdown syntax plus
   tables, task lists, auto-links, and more.</p>

<div class="d-flex align-items-start component-container">
    <div class="p-2 interactivity-card">
        <h5>Markdown Input</h5>
        <textarea class="form-control" rows="14" style="width: 280px; font-family: monospace; font-size: 0.85rem;"
                  @bind=_liveMarkdown @bind:event="oninput"></textarea>
    </div>
    <div class="p-2 flex-grow-1 justify-content-center">
        <h5>Rendered Output</h5>
        <div class="px-0 px-md-3">
            <MarkdownView Markdown=@_liveMarkdown />
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
<hr />

<h4>Default MarkdownView</h4>
<p>Render a Markdown string by passing it to the <code>Markdown</code> parameter.</p>
<pre><code>&lt;MarkdownView Markdown=@("@")_markdownText /&gt;</code></pre>

<MarkdownView Markdown=@_sampleMarkdown />
<hr />

<h4>MarkdownView - Tables</h4>
<p>Tables are supported via the Markdig advanced extensions.</p>
<pre><code>&lt;MarkdownView Markdown=@("@")_tableMarkdown /&gt;</code></pre>

<MarkdownView Markdown=@_tableMarkdown />
<hr />

<h4>MarkdownView - Task Lists</h4>
<p>GitHub-style task lists are supported.</p>
<pre><code>&lt;MarkdownView Markdown=@("@")_taskMarkdown /&gt;</code></pre>

<MarkdownView Markdown=@_taskMarkdown />
<hr />

<h4>MarkdownView - Code Blocks</h4>
<p>Fenced code blocks with language hints are rendered with the <code>&lt;code&gt;</code> element.</p>
<pre><code>&lt;MarkdownView Markdown=@("@")_codeMarkdown /&gt;</code></pre>

<MarkdownView Markdown=@_codeMarkdown />
<hr />
